reviewText: Pretty decent, a little biased, encouraging for ambitious women but perhaps outdated. Worth seeing once. Overall a cool idea for a documentary
this is a wonderful tribute to women in politics.  It is an inspiration to have a glimpse in to the lives of the women - and their families.
I really enjoyed it and learned many things I did not know. I would recommend this DVD to young women.

It was astonishing to my students that at the time of the making of this film that there were only 14 women senators. They asked repeatedly "If there should be 100 senators and half of America is female, why aren't there 50 women senators." The students also thought the women senators dressed very dowdily and thought I should give some fashion tips (colorful clothes and Crocs so their feet wouldn't hurt).

One of my high school social studies teachers asked the library to buy this after seeing it on TV.  She was impressed. We are an all-girls college prep school.  So, finding things to promote women is important to our curriculum.  We also use IRON JAWED ANGELS (fight for women sufferage) in our classes.
